\DOC pp_print_colored_thm

\TYPE {pp_print_colored_thm : formatter -> thm -> unit}

\SYNOPSIS
Prints a theorem to formatter.

\DESCRIBE
The call {pp_print_colored_thm fmt th} prints the colored representation of the
theorem {th} to the formatter {fmt}.
To print without colors, use {pp_print_thm}.

For its color configuration, see {pp_print_colored_type} and {pp_print_colored_term}.

\FAILURE
Should never fail unless the formatter does.

\SEEALSO
pp_print_colored_term, pp_print_colored_type, pp_print_thm, print_thm.

\ENDDOC
